# Windows Security and Reliability

- Validate all external inputs (URLs, process names, paths, hotkey strings) before use.
- Restrict URL launching to approved schemes and reject shell metacharacter patterns.
- Normalize and validate filesystem paths to prevent traversal and unsafe writes.
- For process activation logic, target exact window/process matches and handle missing/closed windows safely.
- Keep native handle lifecycle explicit: register/unregister DWM thumbnails, hooks, and windows predictably.
- Fail safe on interop errors (log, clean up, continue service loop) rather than crashing the app.
- Preserve the rule: no direct client interaction other than foreground activation.
- Never allow mouse/keyboard passthrough from thumbnail surfaces to the source `exefile` window.
- Thumbnail click behavior must only request foreground activation of the source app.
